# API Design

## RESTful Endpoints
- GET /{resources} (list), GET /{resources}/:id (get one)
- POST /{resources} (create), PUT/PATCH /:id (update), DELETE /:id
- Nested: GET /users/:userId/orders
- Actions: POST /:id/activate

## Response Format
- Success: { code, message, data }
- Error: { code, message, data: null }
- Paginated: { code, data: { items, total, page, limit } }

## Query Parameters
- Pagination: ?page=1&limit=10
- Sorting: ?sortBy=field&sortOrder=desc
- Filtering: ?status=active&role=admin
- Search: ?search=keyword

## Best Practices
- Plural nouns, kebab-case URLs
- Version APIs (/api/v1/)
- Validate all inputs
- Document with OpenAPI/Swagger
